# Plesk Firewall rules configuration with dynamic hostnames
# Format: RULE_NAME|DIRECTION|ACTION|PORTS|HOSTNAME|COMMENT
#
# Fields:
#   RULE_NAME  : Unique name for the rule (required)
#   DIRECTION  : input or output (required)
#   ACTION     : allow or deny (required)
#   PORTS      : Port specification (e.g., 22/tcp, 80/tcp,443/tcp) or empty for all ports
#   HOSTNAME   : Dynamic hostname to resolve (required)
#   COMMENT    : Optional description

# Example: Allow SSH from NAS1 (dynamic IP)
# nas1-ssh|input|allow|22/tcp|nas1.example.com|Allow SSH from NAS1

# Example: Allow HTTP and HTTPS from NAS2
# nas2-web|input|allow|80/tcp,443/tcp|nas2.example.com|Allow web from NAS2

# Example: Allow all traffic from NAS1
# nas1-all|input|allow||nas1.example.com|Allow all from NAS1

